<title type="html"><![CDATA[ppu addressing range]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2171&amp;p=18238#p18238"><![CDATA[
Pattern table reads have to come from $0000-$0FFF or $1000-$1FFF - the page selected depends on the bits in $2000.<br /><br />Nametable reads must come from $2000-$2FFF, since it simply uses the active 'VRAM address' (which stores fine Y scroll in the upper bits), ANDs it with $FFF, then ORs it with $2000.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Fri Oct 06, 2006 3:37 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
